						</div>
						<img width="338" height="228" src="https://legionmagazine.com/en/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Canadian-Nurses-memorial-338x228.jpg" class="attachment-338_228 size-338_228 wp-post-image" alt="Canadian Nurses memorial" />						<p>The lonely graves of two Canadian nurses who died during the Gallipoli campaign in the First World War received a new memorial last year, according to the 2014-15 Annual Report of the Commonwealth War Graves Commission (CWGC) released in December. Matron Jessie Jaggard and Nursing Sister Mary Frances Munro both served with the 3rd Canadian Stationary Hospital&#8230;</p>
